div.p: Expansion performed internally based on codesystem NG-Imm Adverse Event Clinical Status CS v0.5.0 (CodeSystem)
This value set contains 6 concepts

tr.td: The clinical condition is currently present, ongoing, or requires active management or monitoring.
The clinical condition is no longer present but is not considered resolved; it may recur or requires no current treatment.
The clinical condition has completely resolved and is no longer impacting the patient's health or requiring further management.
The individual has recovered fully from the adverse event without any long-term effects or sequelae.
The individual has recovered from the adverse event but with lasting effects, complications, or disabilities.
The adverse event resulted in the death of the individual.

div.p: Expansion performed internally based on codesystem NG-Imm Facility Type CS v0.5.0 (CodeSystem)
This value set contains 6 concepts

tr.td: A temporary or mobile health service site established to deliver essential healthcare to underserved or remote populations.
A basic primary healthcare facility providing preventive and promotive services, often staffed by community health workers.
A primary healthcare facility with limited diagnostic and treatment services, typically staffed by nurses, CHEWs, or junior medical personnel.
An advanced primary healthcare facility offering comprehensive outpatient care, minor/light procedures, and referral support, often with a resident medical officer.
A referral facility providing specialized care, inpatient services, and emergency response, staffed by medical officers and specialists.
A highly specialized hospital offering advanced diagnostic, therapeutic, and surgical care, often affiliated with teaching or research institutions.

div.p: Expansion performed internally based on codesystem NG-Imm Vaccine contraindications CS v0.5.0 (CodeSystem)
This value set contains 4 concepts

tr.td: The individual has a weakened immune system due to a medical condition (e.g., cancer, organ transplant, or immunosuppressive therapy), which contraindicates certain live vaccines.
The individual is currently experiencing a severe febrile or respiratory illness (REFI), which may necessitate deferral of immunization until recovery.
The individual has a documented history of a severe allergic (anaphylactic) reaction to a previous dose of a vaccine or any of its components, making re-administration contraindicated.
The individual has symptomatic HIV infection, which may contraindicate live vaccines or require specific vaccine schedules based on immunological status.
